    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix F1AP interface handling error due to missing map_int_to_str function\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP interface was experiencing message loss and corruption downstream of the `map_int_to_str` function call in `openair2/UTIL/OMG/common.c`. Investigation revealed that the function was only available when `STANDALONE` was defined, but was being called in code paths that execute regardless of this condition.\n\nThis fix makes the `map_int_to_str` and `map_str_to_int` functions always available by moving them outside of the `#ifdef STANDALONE` block.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/common.c`: Removed `#ifdef STANDALONE` wrapper around `map_int_to_str` and `map_str_to_int` function definitions\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/defs.h`: Removed `#ifdef STANDALONE` wrapper around `mapping` structure definition and function declarations\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Compile the codebase without `STANDALONE` defined\n2. Run F1AP interface operations that trigger calls to `map_int_to_str`\n3. Observe segmentation faults or undefined behavior due to missing function symbols\n4. Monitor for message loss or corruption in F1AP message handling\n\nThe fix ensures these functions are always linked and available, preventing the downstream issues in F1AP interface handling.\n"
}